# 🔧 CONFIGURATION VARIABLES
Reference for all globally and locally configurable framework variables. Use set [variable] [value] to modify.

---

### 🌐 NETWORKING & RECONNAISSANCE
- LHOST / L_HOST            : Local IP address for reverse connections and C2 callbacks.
- LPORT / L_PORT            : Local listening port for incoming reverse connections.
- R_HOST                    : Remote target IP address, hostname, or CIDR (e.g. 192.168.1.0/24).
- R_MAC                     : Remote target MAC address (Bluetooth or Ethernet).
- R_PORT                    : Remote target port.
- PORT_RANGE                : Ports to scan (e.g. "80,443", "1-1024", or "top").
- THREADS / CONCURRENCY     : Number of concurrent tasks for scanning/recon (default: 500).
- TIMEOUT / SCAN_TIMEOUT    : Network timeout in seconds for probes/scans (default: 1.5).
- INTERFACE                 : Network interface to use for scanning/OTA attacks (e.g., wlan0mon).
- TARGET_BSSID              : Target Wireless Access Point MAC address.
- SOURCE_MAC                : Spoofed source MAC address for OTA frames.

### 📁 MODULE STATE & PAYLOADS
- EXPLOIT                   : Absolute path to the currently loaded exploit module.
- PAYLOAD                   : Absolute path to the currently loaded payload module.
- GENERATED_PAYLOAD         : The raw one-liner for the most recently generated stager.
- RECON_PATH                : Absolute path to the currently loaded reconnaissance module.
- RECON_NAME                : Internal name of the active recon module.
- CVE                       : CVE identifier associated with the current exploit context.
- COMPILER / CC             : Define a custom cross-compiler (e.g., aarch64-linux-android-clang).
- COMP_ARCH                 : Target architecture for the 'compile' command (native, x64, arm64, android_arm64, android_v7).
- COMP_STATIC               : Toggle static linking for the 'compile' command (true/false).
- COMP_OUT                  : Custom output path for the 'compile' command (defaults to payloads/).

### 🧮 KASLR & KERNEL EXPLOITATION
- STATIC_BASE               : Default kernel base address for KASLR offset calculations (hex).
- LEAKED_ADDR               : An address leaked from kernel space used for slide resolution.
- KASLR_SLIDE               : A known slide value used to resolve randomized kernel symbols.
- TARGET_KERNEL             : Targeted kernel version string for build-specific offset lookup.

### 📡 C2 & OPERATIONAL SECURITY
- XOR_KEY                   : Key used for traffic encryption and payload obfuscation.
- OLLVM_ENABLED             : Toggle Obfuscator-LLVM Control Flow Flattening (true/false).
- FRONT_DOMAIN              : Masking domain for SNI-masking / Domain Fronting.
- AUTO_ENUM                 : Toggle automated post-exploitation enumeration (true/false, default: true).
- STAGE2URL                 : URL endpoint where the Stage 2 stager is hosted.
- STAGE_TWO                 : Local file path to the Stage 2 stager binary.
- VERBOSE_LOGGING           : Toggle detailed execution output (true/false).
- DEV_MODE                  : Toggle developer-only diagnostic modes (true/false).
- LISTENER                  : Toggle the framework's background C2 listener (true/false).
- SESSION_ID                : Internal identifier for the active framework session.
- ACTIVE_PROFILE            : Name of the target profile currently loaded in the database.

### 🔑 EXTERNAL APIS & AUTHENTICATION
- SHODAN_API_KEY            : API key for Shodan infrastructure recon and vulnerability mapping.
- GITHUB_TOKEN              : Personal Access Token (PAT) for GitHub API search to bypass rate limits.
- REMOTE_MANIFEST_URL       : (Optional) URL for the central licensing manifest (JSON).

### 📱 ANDROID PAYLOAD GENERATION
- ANDROID_PAYLOAD_TYPE      : APK behavior template (drs, beacon, messages, rootkit).
- APP_NAME                  : Custom title for the installed Android application.
- OUTPUT_NAME               : Custom filename for the generated APK (default: payload.apk).
- SHOW_UI                   : Toggle visible game/app UI on the target device (true/false).
- HIDE_ICON                 : Automatically hide the app icon after first launch (true/false).
- WAKELOCK                  : Request CPU/Power wakelock to prevent Doze termination (true/false).
- ANDROID_API               : Target Android API level for the build (default: 33).
- APK_ARCH                  : Target architecture for native APKs (arm64, armv7, x86_64, all).
- RESULT_SINK               : Webhook URL for data exfiltration callbacks.
- DELAY_SECONDS             : Initial sleep duration for payloads before execution (Ghost architecture).
- EXTERNAL_TASK_URL         : URL for the beacon to poll for external taskings.
- BEACON_MIN_SLEEP          : Minimum seconds for jittered reconnection/check-in.
- BEACON_MAX_SLEEP          : Maximum seconds for jittered reconnection/check-in.

### 🎭 PERSISTENCE & POST-EXPLOITATION
- AGENT_PATH                : Local path to the native agent binary for deployment.
- REMOTE_PATH               : Destination path for the agent on the target device (e.g., /data/local/tmp/agent).
- BOOT_DELAY                : Seconds to wait after boot before triggering the agent (Magisk).
- REBOOT                    : Toggle automatic device reboot after persistence installation (true/false).
- DEVICE_ID                 : Specific ADB serial number to target when multiple devices are connected.

### ⚙️ EXPLOIT-SPECIFIC CONFIG
- COMMAND / CMD             : Single shell command to execute via a remote exploit.
- VID / PID                 : USB Vendor and Product IDs for hardware-level exploits.
- WIPE_FRP                  : Toggle factory reset protection wiping after exploitation (true/false).
- IMAGE_PATH                : Path to a target image for forensic recovery (Acropalypse).
- OUTPUT_PATH / OUTPUT_FILE : Custom destination for exfiltrated data or exploit output.
- PAYLOAD_URL               : Web URL hosting a 2nd-stage payload or exploit trigger.
- ADB_AUTO_SHELL            : Command to run immediately upon ADB Master Key bypass.
- ADB_PAYLOAD_DEPLOY        : Toggle persistent payload installation after ADB bypass.
- PROXY_HOST / PROXY_PORT    : Upstream proxy settings for tunneling traffic through compromised hosts.
- SRVPORT                   : Port for local staging servers (WebKit / Browser exploits).
- RECIPIENT                 : Targeted phone number or handle for messaging exploits.
- TARGET_URI                : Specific Android content provider URI to query.
- HEIMDALL_PATH             : Path to the Heimdall binary for Samsung Odin protocol interaction.
- URL                       : Target URL for browser-based redirection or trigger attacks.
- PORT / BAUD               : Serial port and baud rate for AT command fuzzing (ttyACM0).
- SMB_USER / SMB_PASS       : Credentials for authenticated SMB exploitation (EternalBlue/PrintNightmare).
- SHARE_PATH                : Network share path for driver deployment.

